              },
              "displayName": "Steve Loughran",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Europe/London"
            },
            "body": "There's been some discussion about requesting IO resources in containers: bandwidth/IOPs. It'd be more complex, but\n# gives admins more control over limits\n# allow better performance guarantees for allocated nodes\n# permit cgroup throttling of IO\n# force the container requests to be explicit in their IO needs, for consistent performance on idle/busy nodes\n\nIO resource allocations wouldn't work with HDFS; its a separate process.\n\nAnyway, there is a YARN JIRA somewhere, awaiting someone (you?) to work on it",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=stevel%40apache.org",
              "name": "stevel@apache.org",
              "key": "stevel@apache.org",
